# Typography Rules

## CRITICAL: Only Use Defined Typography Styles

**ALL text in this app MUST use the Arcadia font family through the defined typography system. NEVER use generic fonts like Arial, Helvetica, or system defaults.**

## The Typography System

This design system uses only the Arcadia font family:
- `var(--font-sans)` - Arcadia (for body text)
- `var(--font-display)` - Arcadia Display (for titles/headings)

## Rules

### DO

1. **Use typography CSS classes from `typography.css`** for all text:
   - `.text-title-hero` - Hero titles (34px, Arcadia Display)
   - `.text-title-main` - Main page titles (28px, Arcadia Display)
   - `.text-title-secondary` - Section titles (19px, Arcadia)
   - `.text-title-minor` - Subsection titles (17px, Arcadia)
   - `.text-title-eyebrow` - Eyebrow/overline text (12px, uppercase)
   - `.text-body-lg` / `.text-body-lg-demi` - Large body text (17px)
   - `.text-body` / `.text-body-demi` - Default body text (15px)
   - `.text-body-sm` / `.text-body-sm-demi` - Small body text (14px)
   - `.text-label` / `.text-label-demi` - Labels (13px)
   - `.text-tiny` / `.text-tiny-demi` - Tiny text (12px)
   - `.text-micro` / `.text-micro-demi` - Micro text (10px)

2. **When using inline styles with `fontSize`, ALWAYS include `fontFamily`**:
   ```tsx
   // CORRECT
   style={{ fontFamily: 'var(--font-sans)', fontSize: 15 }}
   
   // WRONG - Will fall back to Arial/system font
   style={{ fontSize: 15 }}
   ```

3. **Use CSS variables for font-family**:
   ```css
   font-family: var(--font-sans);
   font-family: var(--font-display);
   ```

### DON'T

1. **NEVER use generic font-family values**:
   - ❌ `font-family: sans-serif`
   - ❌ `font-family: Arial`
   - ❌ `font-family: Helvetica`
   - ❌ `font-family: system-ui`

2. **NEVER use inline `fontSize` without `fontFamily`**:
   - ❌ `style={{ fontSize: 14 }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ fontSize: '15px' }}`

3. **NEVER add fallback fonts to font-family declarations**:
   - ❌ `font-family: 'Arcadia', sans-serif`
   - ✅ `font-family: 'Arcadia'`

## CSS Class Reference

### In CSS files, always include font-family when setting font-size:

```css
/* CORRECT */
.my-class {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: 15px;
  line-height: 24px;
}

/* WRONG - Missing font-family */
.my-class {
  font-size: 15px;
  line-height: 24px;
}
```

